comment_data.body:
Having the type immediately after the field name without any separation is strange. It's better to put the type in parentheses. For example, the docstring from `nvim_get_hl` `opts` looks like this:
```c
/// @param opts  Options dict:
///                 - name: (string) Get a highlight definition by name.
///                 - id: (integer) Get a highlight definition by id.
///                 - link: (boolean, default true) Show linked group name instead of effective definition |:hi-link|.
///                 - create: (boolean, default true) When highlight group doesn't exist create it.
```

